    BrowserConstants, com.anthem.selenium.constants.EnvConstants

    public class SuperHelper
extends WinSuperHelper
implements BrowserConstants
    This class provides the methods for Selenium and Mainframe using Selenium API. 
     Methods starting with "se" are for standard Selenium only. 
 Methods starting with "seMF" are specifically for Selenium Mainframe.
    Author:
    shiva.katula , gireesh.pawaskar.

      • seOpenBrowserWithBasicAuth

        public static boolean seOpenBrowserWithBasicAuth(String browserName,
                                                 String url,
                                                 String credentialProfile)

        Open a specified web browser to a target URL with Basic Authentication. Use this method only if the application is enabled with Basic Authentication Pop-up. This method exposes User details in URL and make sure of compliance policy to be followed.

        Parameters:
        browserName - 
          String representing the type of browser to open
         
            Chrome as BrowserConstants.Chrome 
        
            Internet Explorer as BrowserConstants.InternetExplorer
        
            HeadLess as BrowserConstants.Headless 
        
            Internet Explorer with Compatibility as BrowserConstants.InternetExplorer_Compatible
        url - String representing the URL to be opened
        credentialProfile - Credential Profile (Shiva_MF) entry from config.properties (eg:- USER_PROFILE = Shiva_MF) Shiva_MF is the name of the properties file from credentials path.
        Returns:
        boolean true/false
